            <title>[CAMEL-5485] camel-mybatis should do a proper transaction demarcation while reading/writing from/to database.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5485</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/MyBatis-Component-Bug-consumer-onConsume-hits-error-transactions-are-committed-instead-of-rollback-td5716774.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/MyBatis-Component-Bug-consumer-onConsume-hits-error-transactions-are-committed-instead-of-rollback-td5716774.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other than DefaultMyBatisProcessingStrategy the same issue exists by MyBatisProducer as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another thing which is currently missing completley is that there&apos;s no transaction demarcation by the Producer at all while &lt;b&gt;reading&lt;/b&gt; from the database, e.g. by SelectOne or SelectList statement types.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
